In a #small pot{}, bring 1 cup water to a boil with a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Add the @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, cover, reduce heat, and simmer until soft, about ~{5%minutes}. Set aside.

Meanwhile, halve, peel, and dice the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced). Core and dice the @roma tomato{1}(core and diced). Dice the @fresh pork chorizo{1}(diced into 1/4-inch pieces). Finely chop the @garlic{1%clove}(minced) and @parsley{1/2%bunch}(finely chopped). Core, seed, and remove the white veins from the @red bell pepper{1}(cored, seeded, and sliced into 1/2-inch cubes). Quarter the @zucchini{1}(quartered lengthwise), then cut into 1/2-inch pieces.

Heat 1/2 tablespoon @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium heat. Add the onion and cook, tossing, until soft, about ~{5%minutes}. Add the chorizo, tomato, and half the garlic to pan. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook until tomato starts to break down, about ~{5%minutes}.

Stir in the cooked bulgur and a pinch of chopped parsley. Season with salt and pepper. Set aside and cover to keep warm.

== Gremolata ==

Make the gremolata: zest and juice half the @lemon{1/2}(zested and juiced) over a #small bowl{}. Add the remaining @parsley{1/2%bunch}(chopped), remaining @garlic{1%clove}(chopped), @olive oil{1%tbsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch} to the bowl. Set aside.

== Vegetables ==

Heat 1 tablespoon @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium heat. Add the bell pepper and zucchini and cook, tossing, until golden brown, ~{4-5%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper and set aside.

== Calamari ==

Slice the @squid{8%ounce} widthwise into 1/2-inch rings. In the same pan you cooked the veggies in, heat 1/2 tablespoon @olive oil{1/2%tbsp} over high heat. Add the squid to the pan and cook, tossing, until lightly golden brown and cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season with salt and pepper.

> Calamari is a very quick-cooking protein, overcooking it could make it tough!

== To Serve ==

Serve the calamari on top of the bulgur mixture with zucchini and peppers to the side. Spoon over the gremolata. Enjoy!